value.name: 199 (number) - Wikipedia
value.snippet: 199 is a centered triangular number. [1] It is a prime number and the fourth part of a prime quadruplet: 191, 193, 197, 199. [2] 199 is the smallest natural number that takes more than two iterations to compute its digital root as a repeated digit sum: Thus, its additive persistence is three, and it is the smallest number of persistence three.
